dcterms:creator: T. Duplessis
dcterms:description: Lichess is the largest open-source online chess platform, hosting almost 100 million games played per month and nearly 2 billion games in total. It provides a diverse set of chess players and allows for the analysis of games played at various time controls, particularly focusing on Blitz games.
dcterms:title: Lichess

dcterms:description: Maia is an open-source version of AlphaZero trained on a population of human players, designed to predict the next move a player of a given skill level will make in a chess position. It significantly improves upon previous models in predicting human moves.
dcterms:title: Maia

dcterms:description: Leela Chess Zero is an open-source implementation of the deep reinforcement learning system AlphaZero for chess. It serves as the foundational code infrastructure for building models that predict human behavior in chess.
dcterms:title: Leela Chess Zero
